<br>
I didn't quad em, but I'm sure you could pretty easily.  Although at 48 most of them started turning lt blue.  But the cash is good and its a nice relaxing, easy camp with not much in the way of risk.<br>
<br>
KEI helps on the down time, you can pretty much do conitnuous pulling on the specs and a sow can be had at the docks at any given moment and a lev doesn't hurt either in case you get into trouble then you can just run across the water and root it or something. <p><center><img src='http://dune.net/~petulant/images/euotis-sig.jpg'><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=301346">Magelo Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhibashira.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/19/02 11:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spec ?</span><hr size=1> I couldn't solo pull them untill they turn light blue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugorams.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gorams</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/24/02 8:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spec ?</span><hr size=1> They were cake for me to solo pull from that island.<br>
